  "texts": [
    "They are designed to securely update and maintain replicated shared states across all peers in the network.",
    "By using consensus methods, the blockchain can ensure that all copies of the shared state agree and synchronize at any given moment, a key aspect of the blockchain's state machine replication system.",
    "According to [49] and [50], deterministic consensus cannot tolerate errors in completely asynchronous communication models.",
    "Therefore, partial synchrony assumptions and maximum latency limits for propagating transactions are necessary [51].",
    "In previous work on consensus procedures, the building elements that went into establishing ''Decentralized'' consensus algorithms utilized in blockchain networks included cryptography and partial synchronous, as well as predecessor designs and suggestions of digital currency [52,53].There are many forms of decentralized blockchain consensus algorithms currently in use, as well as their applicability for IoT networks, particularly in the supply of healthcare services as follows [54]: 1."
  ]
